OL,6,FMr Roffe-Silvester, who was asleep in
OL,7,Fhis own quarters, was woken by noises
OL,8,Fcoming from the boarding house and
OL,9,Fwent to investigate.
OL,11,FWhen he entered the bedroom where the
OL,12,Falleged attack had happened, he saw a
OL,13,Fsilhouetted figure standing in the
OL,14,Froom who turned towards him and
OL,15,Frepeatedly struck him over the head
OL,16,Fwith a hammer.
OL,18,FAnother student heard Mr Roffe-
OL,19,FSilvester's shouts and swearing as he
OL,20,Ffled the bedroom and dialled 999 `
OL,21,Fbelieving there was an intruder.
